*sigh*...  I initially thought that maybe it can be more verbose but healthier to do something like

    startTracing();
    tracing?.dumpLegend();
    stopTracing();

but on top of that there's the arguments that are needed for starting, so it's probably not worth it.  But I still dislike that this goes out of the nice only-start-stop-are-exposed thing...

